o's return for Knox-Johnston Most popular now, in detail New plea on Madeleine's birthday Thatcher unveils Falklands arch Woman destroyed her unborn baby Eurovision's other 'Terry Wogans' Coalition troops missing in Iraq Most popular now, in detail Estonia's statue row: Hand of Moscow or sure vote-winner? Pygmies hold a conference in Congo's tropical rainforest We meet Eurovision commentators from around the continent Back to top ^^ Privacy and cookies policy
http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/rss/-/1/hi/england/beds/bucks/herts/6647995.stm	BBC NEWS | England | Beds/Bucks/Herts | Screening as pupils contract TB Skip to bbc.co.uk navigation Your news when you want it Friday, 11 May 2007, 16:35 GMT 17:35 UK E-mail this to a friend Screening as pupils contract TB Early diagnosis is key to treating TB Pupils and teachers at a junior school are being screened for TB after four pupils tested positive for the disease. A letter was sent to parents of pupils at Southfields Junior School, in Luton, Beds, offering the tests after a pupil displayed symptoms of tuberculosis. Three of his classmates were confirmed to also be in the early stages of the disease, which the Health Protection Agency said is not contracted easily. Luton has three times as many incidents of TB than the national average. The bacteria, which commonly affects the lungs, is on the increase nationally, the Health Protection Agency has said. The affected pupils are being treated with antibiotics and the school has offered the screening as a precaution. E-mail this to a friend BBC Beds Bucks and Herts Travel, leisure, sport, message boards and much more Tuberculosis testing at hospital 11 May 07 | North East/N Isles Tuberculosis cases 'are rising' 22 Mar 07 | Health The BBC is not responsible for the content of external internet sites Two men are charged with murder Euthanasia debate rages a year on Screening as pupils contract TB MOST POPULAR STORIES NOW A pygmy conference in the rainforest Underground search for 'God particle' Zimbabwe to chair major UN body Hero's return for Knox-Johnston Google searches web's dark side Most popular now, in detail New plea on Madeleine's birthday Thatcher unveils Falklands arch Woman destroyed her unborn baby Eurovision's other 'Terry Wogans' Coalition troops missing in Iraq Most popular now, in detail Estonia's statue row: Hand of Moscow or sure vote-winner? Pygmies hold a conference in Congo's tropical rainforest We meet Eurovision comm